@startuml HealSense_Hardware_Circuit
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml
LAYOUT_TOP_DOWN()
title HealSense: Hardware Circuit Schematic & Sensor Connectivity

package "Power Management" as power {
    component "5V Power Supply\n(Battery/USB/Adapter)" as psu
    component "Voltage Regulator\n(LDO 3.3V)" as vreg
    component "Decoupling Capacitors\n(100uF + 10uF)" as caps
}

package "Microcontroller Unit" as mcu_pkg {
    component "ESP32\n(Main MCU)" as esp32
}

package "I2C Sensor Bus\n(Address: 0x57-0x68)" as i2c_bus {
    component "MAX30100\nPulse Oximeter\n(HR + SpO₂)\nAddr: 0x57" as max30100
    component "MLX90614\nIR Thermometer\n(Temperature)\nAddr: 0x5A/0x5B" as mlx90614
    component "BMP180/BMP280\nBarometric Sensor\n(Pressure)\nAddr: 0x77" as bmp
    component "I2C Pullup Resistors\n(4.7kΩ × SDA/SCL)" as pullups
}

package "UART Communication" as uart {
    component "ESP32 UART0\n(RX0=GPIO3, TX0=GPIO1)" as uart_debug
}

package "Wireless Module" {
    component "ESP32 WiFi\n(Built-in 802.11b/g/n)" as wifi
    component "ESP32 BLE\n(Bluetooth 5.0)" as ble
}

package "Monitoring & Indicator" as monitor {
    component "Status LED\n(GPIO27, Blue)" as led_status
    component "Error LED\n(GPIO26, Red)" as led_error
    component "100Ω Current Limiting\nResistor" as resistor
}

' Power connections
psu --> vreg: 5V input
vreg --> esp32: 3.3V output
vreg --> caps: Stabilization
caps --> esp32: Power supply

' MCU to sensors
esp32 --> i2c_bus: SDA (GPIO21)\nSCL (GPIO22)
pullups --> i2c_bus: Pull SDA/SCL to 3.3V

' Sensors on I2C bus
i2c_bus --> max30100: I2C addr 0x57
i2c_bus --> mlx90614: I2C addr 0x5A
i2c_bus --> bmp: I2C addr 0x77

' UART for debugging
esp32 --> uart_debug: Debug output

' Wireless (built-in)
esp32 --> wifi: Integrated module
esp32 --> ble: Integrated module

' Status indicators
esp32 --> led_status: GPIO27
esp32 --> led_error: GPIO26
resistor --> led_status
resistor --> led_error

note right of max30100
MAX30100 PINOUT:
- VCC → 3.3V
- GND → GND
- SDA → GPIO21
- SCL → GPIO22
- INT → GPIO35 (optional)

Readings every 100ms
HR: 30-240 bpm
SpO2: 70-100%
end note

note right of mlx90614
MLX90614 PINOUT:
- VCC → 3.3V
- GND → GND
- SDA → GPIO21
- SCL → GPIO22
- PWM → GPIO33 (optional)

Temperature: -40 to +125°C
Accuracy: ±0.5°C
I2C frequency: 100 kHz
end note

note right of bmp
BMP180/280 PINOUT:
- VCC → 3.3V
- GND → GND
- SDA → GPIO21
- SCL → GPIO22

Pressure: 300-1100 hPa
Temperature: -40 to +125°C
I2C frequency: 100 kHz
end note

note right of esp32
ESP32 PIN MAPPING:
GPIO1: TX0 (Debug)
GPIO3: RX0 (Debug)
GPIO21: SDA (I2C)
GPIO22: SCL (I2C)
GPIO26: Error LED
GPIO27: Status LED
GPIO33: PWM (optional)
GPIO35: Interrupt input

Power: 3.3V ± 10%
Current: 80mA (WiFi active)
                40mA (BLE only)
end note

note bottom of i2c_bus
I2C SPECIFICATIONS:
- Standard Mode: 100 kHz
- Pullup: 4.7kΩ to 3.3V
- Max devices: 127 (addr 0x00-0x7F)
- Clock stretching: Supported
- Multi-master: Supported
end note

note bottom of power
POWER REQUIREMENTS:
Input: 5V DC (USB/Battery)
Output: 3.3V regulated
Capacity: ≥1A for full operation
With WiFi active: 500mA peak
All sensors idle: 50mA
Always-on features: <10mA
end note

@enduml
